<br>
1) has been an issue for a long long time. they even claimed to have fixed it but the only thing they seem to have fixed is the &quot;you can't see your target from there&quot; message you used to get. Nobody is sure why you can't cast thru the water surface, however I suspect there must've been some pulling exploit issue from long long ago, during beta.<br>
<br>
2) the %M command returns the name of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>YOUR PET</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, not a pet you happen to have targeted. If you have no pet up it returns Pet. They don't always make that clear in their manuals and help screens. If the mage uses it, it works, but for the cleric it doesn't. The cleric needs to use the double F-key to target the pet and %T to get the pet name to show up in the healing macro. <p><br>
