<br>
If you give a pet armor before handing the weapons, the pet won't equip the weapons.  I can't explain why, but it just never will.  So to avoid this, always give it weapons first, then armor.  (but I wonder, does giving weapons then armor mean it doesn't use some of the armor?)<br>
<br>
Anything that will add the Master to the pet's hate list will always make the pet poof.  This includes attacking Eyes of Zomm, getting hit in duels, etc.  Not sure if Cancel Magic on yourself will do this too, since Cancel Magic is a hostile spell now.<br>
<br>
CotHing kills pets because that's part of the aggro-wipe function, I don't see this getting changed (Nor do I see it as a bug really).<br>
<br>
As stated before, Eye of Tallon's invisibility component causes pets to poof.  Similarly, this isn't improved invis, and as such wears off at random times (&quot;You feel yourself starting to appear&quot;) which can cause the Eye to poof.  Also, because of the invisibility component, casting any spells or otherwise breaking invis will make the Eye poof.  Simply removing the invisibility component would solve all three problems.<br>
<br>
Probably not a bug, but our pets haven't talked for a LONG time now.  I miss that, seeing stuff like &quot;Time to die, a moss snake!&quot;, or &quot;Thanks for the Lion Meat, Nirrudn.&quot;  Would be nice to get that back, unless it screws up Voice Graft or something. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=imaginos9>Imaginos9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The UI Guy</span><br>  Posts: 979<br> <font color=#333333>(10/26/02 12:27:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=450.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Nirrudn, <br>
